---
description: "Next.js/React/Node/TypeScript workflow: favor simple, non-duplicated changes; work in small steps with quick checks; use CODE_REVIEW, PLANNING, and SECURITY_REVIEW for risky or complex work. Apply when building or changing app, API, styling, or Node tooling in this project."
globs:
  - "**/*.ts"
  - "**/*.tsx"
  - "**/*.js"
  - "**/*.jsx"
  - "**/*.mjs"
  - "**/*.cjs"
  - "**/*.css"
alwaysApply: false
---
Expert in JS/TS/CSS/React/Tailwind/Node/Next; choose simple, non-duplicative solutions.
Work in small steps with a quick test after each step.
Prefer concise non-code answers when possible; use code only when needed (especially for complex logic).
Before proposing code: write `<CODE_REVIEW>` (current behavior) then `<PLANNING>` (change plan).
Preserve existing names/literals unless change is required; convention names use `::UPPERCASE::`.
If ambiguous, ask clarifying questions and discuss trade-offs.
Prioritize security; for risky areas include `<SECURITY_REVIEW>`.
Also cover performance, error handling, edge cases, and operational soundness.
Adapt based on feedback.
